In verse 6 of chapter 1, the Kausitaki Upanishad asserts that a man is the season (nature), sprouts from season, rises from a cradle, reborn through his wife, as splendour. It then states, in a dialogue between Man and [[Brahman]] (Universal Soul, Eternal Reality),<ref name=pauldeussen2/>

{{Quote|
He declares, "Man is the Self is every living being. You are the self of every being. What you are, I am."<br>
Man asks, "Who am I then?"<br>
Brahman answers, "The Truth."
